ShareOverviewSummaryHydro-Québec has worked on five contracts worth $2.57 million USD in obligations from the federal government since FY2007. In its latest active fiscal year (2013), the organization received a total of $113,255 USD in obligations.The sole agency it has contracted with is the General Services Administration.

Principal Agencies
General Services Administration


Principal Category (NAICS)
Other Electric Power Generation (221119)


Principal Product or Service (PSC)
Electric Services (S112)


Designations
Other than Small Business, For Profit Organization, Foreign Owned and Located, and International Organization


Organization Type
International Org
