Hydro-Québec is a Canadian utility company that specializes in generating, transmitting and distributing electricity. Based in Montreal, it is a Crown corporation and serves all of Quebec and some other provinces of Canada. It invests heavily in research and development.
Hydro-Québec is a Canadian utility company that specializes in generating, transmitting and distributing electricity. Based in Montreal, it serves all of Quebec and some other provinces of Canada. It invests heavily in research and development.

Hydro-Québec’s Information Technology department operates out of… MoreHydro-Québec is a Canadian utility company that specializes in generating, transmitting and distributing electricity. Based in Montreal, it serves all of Quebec and some other provinces of Canada. It invests heavily in research and development.

Hydro-Québec’s Information Technology department operates out of the company's Montreal headquarters. It is a centralized system, with all key decision makers located in Montreal. The main role of the department is internal support/ training, infrastructure/ security, and business operations.

There is a very strong emphasis on SAP technology, particularly for financial and HR purposes. The company operates on SAP-based servers and IBM SAN data storage equipment.

Hydro-Quebec operates its own telecom network. It transmits strategic data (e.g. for the supervisory control systems) and to enable verbal communications among utility personnel. Whether in urban centers or in remote areas, some 20,000 employees can talk to each other via this network. In fact, the telecommunications network covers more than half of the province. Network signals are transmitted over more than 16,000 circuits using fiber-optic links, microwave and telephone cables. 

They use cloud and cluster technology and have virtualized (using Hyper-V components). Security is a primary focus and they will continue to invest in that area.





